# Studify — Awwwards Transformation Rules

You are transforming a basic Next.js 14 scaffolding into an Awwwards Site of the Day quality experience.
The scaffolding was generated by Antigravity and has working routing, data, components.
Your job is NOT to rebuild — it's to TRANSFORM each section into something extraordinary.

## Brand (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- Primary: #FF8225 (orange). Light theme. White backgrounds.
- Text: #1A1108. Secondary: #6B6560. Never pure black or white.
- Dark sections allowed ONLY for: footer, contrast stats blocks.

## Design DNA
- Reference: Shopify BFCM Globe (3D hero) + Education Above All (emotional scroll) + Stripe (premium clean)
- Every section must have ONE unique interaction that makes it memorable
- Typography is the backbone — if it doesn't look great at 120px with no images, the design fails
- Whitespace is generous — 120px+ between sections, 80px+ internal padding
- Animations serve the story, not decoration

## Tech Rules
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger for ALL scroll-driven animations
- Framer Motion for component state only (hover, open/close, mount)
- React Three Fiber for 3D globe
- Lenis for smooth scroll
- Only animate transform + opacity. Never layout properties.
- Always: @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { animation: none; transition: none; }
- Clean up all GSAP instances in useEffect return
- Mobile-first. Test at 375px.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict. No 'any'.
- Tailwind classes. No inline styles except GSAP-manipulated refs.
- "use client" only where needed.
- Dynamic imports for heavy components (Globe, ChatWidget).